column5: Managed 2 for the day with a personal best with this beautifull monster! Still more fishing to be had out there so dress up and enjoy
Great fish and pics!!!  That's a Hugh Jass Mucksie!

Mr. Twister.  My wife and I visit Rideau Ferry every July and have for the past 8-9 years, primarily for bass  (Maple Crest Motel and Cabins).  The camp owner knows I make trips to the French each year for musky.  He keeps saying there are musky in the Rideau and that I don't have to drive all the way to the French.  He keeps telling me I need to take some time and try for some skis on the Rideau.  Unfortunately, there aren't any in the area that we visit - that I know of.   Looks like I'll need to do a bit of homework and just see where these girls live and give it a shot some time.  Won't be up in July this year, due to a change in plans, but maybe in September.  That is one very nice ski and my hat's off to you.
Very, VERY nice ! Guess I should spend more time down there when I visit Mom in SF or daughter in Ottawa!
That's a big momma isn't it? I know you're not going to tell us where, but what did you catch that beauty on? Thanks for posting that Rideau monster.
THAT is what fall Muskie fishing is all about!
Holy S**T!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! nice fish! Ottawa is good for something after all.
And it aint hockey!.....(Damn my leafs!!!!)
Nice Ski! Now I feel like going for one more muskie trip!
WHOA!!! Nice fat muskie!  Congrats on a great catch!
A very nice fall musky !!!!!! congrats,  a great way to finish off the 2007 fishing season,for being in a boat i mean .... nice pics as well,  cheers
PIG Fish. WTG.  GPS co-ord's anyone???  lol.
